fees.description: BPay payments incur a $2.50 (inc GST) fee per transaction.

electricityContract.terms: See our full terms and conditions at www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information. If you are eligible, you can apply to receive QLD Government energy rebates when you sign up with us.
electricityContract.variation: We may vary your rates and charges by providing you notice of any changes at least 10 business days before the change is effective and in any event no later than your next bill such as for tariff reassignments.

incentives.description: From time to time, Dodo Power & Gas may provide promotional offers (including one-off payments and/or products) though promotional codes, which may be redeemed when signing up. These codes do not change the rates, fees or charges of this offer.

singleRate.description: Supply will be available for a minimum 8 hours per day, at the discretion of the distributor, generally between 10pm and 7am.
Supply will be available for a minimum 18 hours per day, at the absolute discretion of the distributor.

solarFeedInTariff.description: Retailer Feed-in Tariff - This plan is available to eligible small solar customers with a maximum 10kW panel size and an inverter system no greater than 10kW as part of an ongoing contract.

electricityContract.onExpiryDescription: No Term contracts do not expire until you notify us in accordance with our Energy Market Contract Terms and Conditions.
electricityContract.additionalFeeInformation: For further details on the information and fees presented, or the terms and conditions of the contract, please visit www.dodo.com/energy/terms-prices-and-regulatory-information or contact us on 13 dodo (13 36 36).
